alert.note: Alert for Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 05 at 2:30AM PST until January 05 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca zone. * WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 1 PM PST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Tidal overflow around high tide may cause flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
